    "John Trapp": "If ye then be risen with Christ ] As ye profess to be, #Col 2:12 . Seek those things, &amp;c. ] As Christ risen spake and did only the things pertaining to the kingdom of God, #Ac 1:3 , and waited alway for his exaltation into heaven; there should be continual ascensions in our hearts. The Church is compared to pillars of smoke, elationibus fumi, #So 3:6 , as having her affections, thoughts, desires upward, heavenward. (Tremel.)\nVer.\n1. Reverence; \"Let the wife see that she reverence her husband,\" #Eph 5:33 , as Sarah `[char_Sarah_Ref]` did, and is chronicled for it, #1Pe 3:6 . But God hath a barren womb for mocking Michal.\n1. If ye then be risen with Christ] As ye profess to be, #Col 2:\n1. Reverence; \"Let the wife see that she [v_Eph_5_33] reverence her husband,\" #Eph 5:33, as Sarah `[char_Sarah_Ref]` did, and is chronicled for it, #1Pe 3:"
